  "prompt": "Can an L2 visa holder work without EAD?",
  "response": "An L-2 visa holder can work in the United States without needing an Employment Authorization Document (EAD) if they are the spouse of an L-1 visa holder. L-2 visa holders are eligible to apply for an EAD, but they do not need one to work if their EAD application has been approved. It\u2019s important to note that the ability to work is contingent upon having the EAD; without it, L-2 holders are not authorized to work. \n\nHowever, children holding L-2 visas are not eligible to work until they reach age 18, even if they have an EAD. \n\nAlways check the most current regulations or consult an immigration attorney for specific advice related to your situation.",
